<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: New povar guild. Sick of it all?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Everum">Everum</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 6:09 a.m. 27/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: New povar guild. Sick of it all?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/povar.cgi?read=122" TARGET=_self>New povar guild. Sick of it all?</A> (Crysta)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR><font size="2" face="arial">If you intend on creating a guild based on hate, please allow me to offer this tiny advice. Don't. Why not create one based on your beliefs of kind-heartiness and good? I know there are individuals out there who lead a chaotic path and I have dealt with or seen situations like yours before. Nevertheless, you should never give up. I haven't.
<P>As far as guilds go, they are created mainly to establish reputation only. Keep that in mind. I normally tend to stick with parties, and not ally myself with guilds. They are rigid in their rules and when you have to go to war, you go. :-)
<P>If you intend on creating this guild, change your views. I would gladly lend my services to you. Have to run. Keep in contact.
<P>-- Level 1 Paladin Apprentice-to-be
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
